```{r, echo = FALSE}
library(plotly)
library(cowplot)
#library(prettydoc)
#source("~/Dropbox/bamm_rpanda/R/base_for_panels_rpanda.R")
#source("~/Dropbox/bamm_rpanda/R/base_for_panels_bamm.R")
```

This is just a testing post to check whether I can embed interactive
plots made with [ggplot2](http://ggplot2.org/) +
[plotly](https://plot.ly/ggplot2/).
The results presented here belong to an ongoing project that is part
of my PhD dissertation, and the code for it can be found
[here](https://github.com/gburin/bamm_rpanda).

## Parameter Space

### BVARDCST

```{r, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
ggplotly(parspace.bvdc)
```

### BCSTDVAR

```{r, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
ggplotly(parspace.bcdv)
```

### Number of Tips

```{r, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
ggplotly(ntip.plot)
```

### Tree Length

```{r, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
ggplotly(length.plot)
```

### Corrected Gamma at 80% loss

```{r, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
ggplotly(gamma.plot)
```

## Fitting

### BVARDCST

#### 20% loss

##### RPANDA

```{r, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
ggplotly(rpanda.bvdc.ndf.20.all + theme_cowplot(font_size = 10))
```

```{r, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
ggplotly(rpanda.bvdc.ndf.20.all.diff.point + theme_cowplot(font_size = 10))
```

##### BAMM

```{r, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
ggplotly(bamm.bvdc.ndf.20.all + theme_cowplot(font_size = 10))
```

```{r, echo = FALSE, warning = FALSE, message = FALSE}
ggplotly(bamm.bvdc.ndf.20.all.diff.point + theme_cowplot(font_size = 10))
```

